node.text: ELLE.com here, your one and only source into the fabulous life of @WhitneyPeak, star of HBO Max’s @GossipGirl. Spotted on the July Digital Cover, she’s letting ELLE #AskMeAnything. Tune in as she dishes on her dream scene partner, her favorite OG 'Gossip Girl’ scene and the song that serves as her current theme song. XOXO. #GossipGirl

node.text: @MadisonBeer's must-haves for a relaxing day off? Sleeping in, sweats, and skincare galore. The singer/songwriter recently added co-founder to her résumé with the launch of her skincare line, #KNOWBeauty, and today she's showing it off to ELLE (along with a glimpse of her insane closet) on #WakingUpWith.

node.title: This Is Madison Beer's Morning Routine | Waking Up With

node.text: 15 words. 10 seconds on the clock. Can @anthonyramosofficial join the #SongAssociation rankings? The #InTheHeights star and all around music master is up for the challenge! node.text: It's been quite a year for @AnyaTaylorJoy​. The actress gained global recognition for her incredible performance in the most-talked about series of 2020 – #TheQueensGambit​ – while sweeping up awards, and even sending chess set sales through the roof. The May cover star sits down with ELLE for #AskMeAnything​, chatting with us about Robert De Niro, what makes her nostalgic, and the movie scene that gets her every time.

node.title: Ask Me Anything with Anya Taylor-Joy

node.text: May cover star @OliviaRodrigo​ is taking the wheel on #SongAssociation​! The talented newcomer has become one of *the* biggest pop stars in the world, making history as both of her debut smash hits, #driverslicense​ and #dejavu​, sit at the top of the charts. Tune in on this episode as she sings #TaylorSwift​, dishes on her dream collaboration, her first concert, and the song she wishes she wrote.

node.text: Today we're in the kitchen with @pepperthai2! The internet's favorite matriarch and culinary enthusiast is showing us how to whip up one of her signatures (and @chrissyteigen’s favorite) – a mouthwatering Pad Korat recipe – straight from her new cookbook, #ThePepperThaiCookbook. Eat up!

node.title: Pepper Teigen Shares Her Pad Korat Recipe

node.text: Sunisa Lee has won gold in the gymnastics all-around final, making history as the first Hmong American to become an Olympic champion. “People hate on [Asians] for no reason," Lee told ELLE in May. "It would be cool to show that we are more than what they say." Lee's father John, who became paralyzed after an accident in 2019, said their Hmong community back in Minnesota was rooting for his daughter. If she won, John said at the time, “it would be the greatest accomplishment of any Hmong person in the U.S. ever. It will go down in history.” Click the link in bio to read more of her journey to Olympic gold.

node.text: Two of the world’s most prominent athletes, Simone Biles and Naomi Osaka, are no longer bound for the tallest spot on the podium at the Tokyo Olympics. “The losses were heart-wrenching. They were unexpected. But they were not, as many have tried to suggest, an affront to the sport,” @laurpuckett writes. “How many more of these public meltdowns will it take for us to understand? These women do not owe us a win at the cost of their lives.” At the link in bio, why the ultimate hypocrisy leaves only ourselves to blame.

node.text: Low-rise jeans are back, people! From velour tracksuits to UGGs, fashion crazes of the early aughts have made a triumphant return. And while pelvis-skimming denim is a hard sell, thinking we can stem the tide of these revivals shows a misunderstanding of how fashion works. This is what always happens: every era brings once-reviled items we’d forsworn to our metaphorical donation pile back to the surface. Grab your Razr flip phones and head to the link in bio. 👖#regram

node.text: Among @hermes’s over 50 styles, you’re likely most familiar with the Birkin and the Kelly, which have certainly gotten the most pop-culture airtime, whether it’s Rory Gilmore receiving a birthday Birkin or Grace Kelly modeling what would later become her name- sake bag against the Riviera backdrop of Hitchcock’s To Catch a Thief. But there is a formidable, equally beloved entourage waiting in the wings, from the Garden Party, a sturdy tote originally designed to carry gardeners’ tools, to the Constance, named for the designer’s daughter. “They are all different stories,” executive VP Catherine Fulconis says, “but they all breathe Hermès.” Click the link in bio for the stories behind their creation.

node.text: The protective style of the summer? Feed-in braids. 🔥 This styling method earned it’s moniker due to “feeding-in” pieces of hair to the main braid to gradually grow in size—all while maintaining a more natural look at the hairline (especially when using synthetic braiding hair). Another pro? Since your braid size gradually scales, it protects your edges from excessive tension from too heavy extensions. Click the link in bio for 20 styles to bookmark now. #regram
